# Cursor AI Settings
# Auto-accept and run all tool calls by default

## Default Behavior
- Auto-accept all file edits
- Auto-run terminal commands
- Auto-install dependencies
- Skip confirmation prompts when safe

## Preferences
- Prefer creating new files over editing existing ones when appropriate
- Use modern Next.js patterns (App Router, Server Components)
- Always include TypeScript types
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Prefer free/open-source services

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Prefer async/await over promises
- Use Next.js 14+ App Router conventions
- Use Prisma for database operations
- Use server actions for mutations

## Auto-actions
- Run npm install automatically when package.json changes
- Run prisma generate when schema changes
- Deploy to Vercel when ready
- Create git commits automatically

